        <summary>How do cyclical stocks differ from defensive stocks?</summary>
        <p>While cyclical stocks provide discretionary goods that consumers cut back on during hard times, defensive stocks provide essential goods (like utilities and basic food) that consumers need regardless of the economy, making them much more stable during recessions.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
